<plot>September 4, 1995, Stoney Point Natives assemble at Ipperwash Provincial Park, near Sarnia, Ontario, Canada, for what began as a peaceful protest. What was to be a reclamation of an indian burial ground, turned into a killing of One Dead Indian, at the hands of an Ontario Provincial Police officer. The story continues through the investigation into one of Canada's bloodiest days.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?412026</url></doc>
